he command fails.\n- `--transcript-path` is required.\n- Session data is always written to the `project` target.\n- `--associate-target` optionally adds a relationship from another explicit\n  GitMeta target to the project session key.\n- GitMeta writes use shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys.\n- The command does not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta.\n\n## Do Not Implement Yet\n\n- No Cursor suppo\n[TRUNCATED]\n on `but-api`, `but-db`, `but-ctx`, `but-claude`, `but-cursor`,\n  or legacy virtual branch APIs.\n- No inferred branch, PR, change, or commit association keys.\n\n## Dependency Decision\n\nUse the GitMeta GitHub repository pinned to an explicit revision:\n\n```toml\ngit-meta-lib = { git = \"https://github.com/git-meta/git-meta.git\", rev = \"[REDACTED:entropy]\" }\n```\n\nDo not use a local path dependency for the POC, and do not float the dependency\non a branch. When updating GitMeta intentionally, replace the pinned revision\nwith the desired upstream commit.\n\n## CLI Contract\n\n```text\nbut agentlog capture [--agent <codex|claude>] --transcript-path <path> [--associate-target <target>]\n```\n\n| Option                             | POC behavior                                                                                  |\n| ---------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `--agent codex` / `--agent claude` | Optional when the invoking agent is detected. Other values fail as unsupported.                |\n| `--transcript-path <path>`         | Required. Must point to a readable JSONL transcript for the selected agent.                    |\n| `--associate-target <target>`      | Optional. Adds `gitbutler:agent-sessions += <session-key>` to that explicit GitMeta target.    |\n\nDefault human/shell output is a single terse line. JSON output is the same\nmessage in an object so hooks do not need to parse prose:\n\n```text\nCaptured 42 records\nCaptured 42 records and associated session with branch:main\n```\n\n```json\n{\n\t\"message\": \"Captured 42 records\"\n}\n```\n\nNormal human output, JSON output, and validation errors should not include full\ntranscript paths.\n\n## Agent Transcript Parsing\n\nPOC parser reads JSONL line by line from one byte snapshot. Empty lines are\nignored. A malformed final non-empty line is treated as a partial write and\nskipped; a malformed earlier line fails.\n\nRecord indexes are 0-based over non-empty JSONL records.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T08:20:53.490Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}